        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(daemon): write Windows Scheduled Task XML as UTF-16",
        "body": "Fixes #315.\n\nWindows Task Scheduler can reject task XML whose declared encoding does not match its on-disk bytes, especially on non-UTF-8 system code pages. Write the generated task definition as BOM-marked UTF-16LE and declare UTF-16 explicitly.\n\nThis also preserves localized account names and non-ASCII launcher paths instead of relying on the active ANSI code page.\n\nValidation:\n\n- `pnpm -s check`\n- Native Windows: focused tests passed; `summarize daemon install` registered the task from a non-ASCII profile path; BOM, declaration, decoded path, task query, and cleanup verified.\n",
